Index entries for sequences related to groups
formula: a(n) = n^9*Product_{primes p dividing n} ((1 - 1/p^3)*(1 - 1/p^2)*(1 - 1/p)). This also gives a formula for A011785.
Multiplicative with a(p^e) = p^(9*e-6)*(p^3 - 1)*(p^2 - 1)*(p - 1). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Nov 18 2001
mathematica: a[n_] := n^9*Times @@ Function[p, (1 - 1/p^3)*(1 - 1/p^2)*(1 - 1/p)] /@ FactorInteger[n][[All, 1]]; a[1] = 1; Array[a, 20] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Mar 21 2017 *)
program: (PARI) a(n) = n^9*prod(k=2, n, if (!isprime(k) || (n % k), 1, (1-1/k^3)*(1-1/k^2)*(1-1/k))); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 30 2015
